{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-08",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_08_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 8 - Horsefeathers",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 5,
  "page_start_sec": 249.344,
  "page_end_sec": 490.06,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.672,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 249.344,
      "end": 250.16,
      "text": "I dare say",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 250.72,
      "end": 252.46,
      "text": "they would have murdered me then and there."
    },
    {
      "start": 254.06,
      "end": 255.44,
      "text": "When he went out to answer the bell,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 255.84,
      "end": 258.24,
      "text": "he left her here with the pistol to watch over me."
    },
    {
      "start": 259.808,
      "end": 261.68,
      "text": "Bridget O'Shaughnessy jumped out of the armchair,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 261.72,
      "end": 262.0,
      "text": "crying,"
    },
    {
      "start": 262.688,
      "end": 266.14,
      "text": "\"'Why don't you tell the truth?' and slapped Cairo on the cheek.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 267.296,
      "end": 268.76,
      "text": "Cairo yelled inarticulately.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 269.664,
      "end": 272.1,
      "text": "Dundee pushed the girl back into the chair with the hand",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 272.1,
      "end": 274.42,
      "text": "that was not holding the Levantine's arm and growled,"
    },
    {
      "start": 275.104,
      "end": 275.87,
      "text": "\"'None of that now.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 276.64,
      "end": 277.42,
      "text": "Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 277.54,
      "end": 278.46,
      "text": "lighting his cigarette,"
    },
    {
      "start": 278.68,
      "end": 281.08,
      "text": "grinned softly through smoke and told Tom,"
    },
    {
      "start": 282.112,
      "end": 283.04,
      "text": "\"'She's impulsive.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 283.52,
      "end": 285.02,
      "text": "\"'Yeah,' Tom agreed."
    },
    {
      "start": 285.984,
      "end": 287.76,
      "text": "Dundee scowled down at the girl and asked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 288.86,
      "end": 290.76,
      "text": "\"'What do you want us to think the truth is?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 292.08,
      "end": 294.02,
      "text": "\"'Not what he said,' she replied.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 294.688,
      "end": 296.06,
      "text": "\"'Not anything he said.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 296.66,
      "end": 297.5,
      "text": "She turned to Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 298.36,
      "end": 298.76,
      "text": "\"'Is it?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 299.64,
      "end": 301.28,
      "text": "\"'How do I know?' Spade said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 302.08,
      "end": 304.82,
      "text": "\"'I was out in the kitchen mixing an omelette when it all happened,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 304.9,
      "end": 305.52,
      "text": "wasn't I?'"
    },
    {
      "start": 306.52,
      "end": 307.54,
      "text": "She wrinkled her forehead,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 307.78,
      "end": 310.44,
      "text": "studying him with eyes that perplexity clouded."
    },
    {
      "start": 311.392,
      "end": 312.72,
      "text": "Tom grunted in disgust.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 313.38,
      "end": 313.86,
      "text": "Dundee,"
    },
    {
      "start": 314.0,
      "end": 315.52,
      "text": "still scowling down at the girl,"
    },
    {
      "start": 315.68,
      "end": 317.88,
      "text": "ignored Spade's speech and asked her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 318.4,
      "end": 320.3,
      "text": "If he's not telling the truth,"
    },
    {
      "start": 320.52,
      "end": 323.36,
      "text": "how come he did the squawking for help and not you?"
    },
    {
      "start": 324.74,
      "end": 325.02,
      "text": "Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 325.24,
      "end": 327.52,
      "text": "he was scared to death when I struck him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 328.04,
      "end": 328.42,
      "text": "she replied,"
    },
    {
      "start": 328.54,
      "end": 329.94,
      "text": "looking contemptuously at the"
    },
    {
      "start": 330.1,
      "end": 330.52,
      "text": "Levantine."
    },
    {
      "start": 331.68,
      "end": 334.12,
      "text": "Cairo's face flushed where it was not blood-smeared.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 334.72,
      "end": 335.58,
      "text": "He exclaimed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 336.06,
      "end": 336.36,
      "text": "Foo!"
    },
    {
      "start": 336.7,
      "end": 337.62,
      "text": "Another lie!"
    },
    {
      "start": 339.14,
      "end": 340.06,
      "text": "She kicked his leg,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 340.24,
      "end": 343.42,
      "text": "the high heel of her blue slipper striking him just below the knee."
    },
    {
      "start": 344.42,
      "end": 346.1,
      "text": "Dundee pulled him away from her while",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 346.1,
      "end": 348.04,
      "text": "Big Tom came to stand close to her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 348.1,
      "end": 348.42,
      "text": "rumbling."
    },
    {
      "start": 349.2,
      "end": 349.8,
      "text": "Behave,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 349.8,
      "end": 350.04,
      "text": "sister."
    },
    {
      "start": 350.28,
      "end": 351.6,
      "text": "That's no way to act."
    },
    {
      "start": 352.9,
      "end": 354.22,
      "text": "Then make him tell the truth,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 354.92,
      "end": 355.32,
      "text": "she said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 356.4,
      "end": 356.88,
      "text": "We'll do that,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 356.94,
      "end": 357.28,
      "text": "all right,"
    },
    {
      "start": 357.44,
      "end": 358.12,
      "text": "he promised."
    },
    {
      "start": 358.32,
      "end": 359.6,
      "text": "Just don't get rough."
    },
    {
      "start": 360.68,
      "end": 361.28,
      "text": "Dundee,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 361.4,
      "end": 363.3,
      "text": "looking at Spade with green eyes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 363.36,
      "end": 364.96,
      "text": "hard and bright with satisfaction,"
    },
    {
      "start": 365.48,
      "end": 366.8,
      "text": "addressed his subordinate."
    },
    {
      "start": 367.64,
      "end": 368.02,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 368.08,
      "end": 368.38,
      "text": "Tom,"
    },
    {
      "start": 368.56,
      "end": 369.96,
      "text": "I guess we'll take them in."
    },
    {
      "start": 371.264,
      "end": 372.36,
      "text": "Tom nodded gloomily.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 373.21,
      "end": 376.26,
      "text": "Spade left the door and advanced to the center of the room,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 376.7,
      "end": 379.62,
      "text": "dropping a cigarette into a tray on the table as he passed it."
    },
    {
      "start": 380.66,
      "end": 382.94,
      "text": "His smile and manner were amiable and easy.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 384.352,
      "end": 385.96,
      "text": "\"'Don't be in a hurry,' he said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 386.432,
      "end": 387.88,
      "text": "\"'Everything can be explained.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 389.152,
      "end": 390.78,
      "text": "\"'I bet you,' Dundee agreed,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 391.06,
      "end": 391.48,
      "text": "sneering."
    },
    {
      "start": 392.512,
      "end": 393.7,
      "text": "Spade bowed to the girl.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 394.944,
      "end": 396.6,
      "text": "\"'Miss O'Shaughnessy,' he said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 397.3,
      "end": 400.94,
      "text": "\"'May I present Lieutenant Dundee and Detective Sergeant Polehouse?'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 401.62,
      "end": 402.9,
      "text": "He bowed to Dundee.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 403.72,
      "end": 406.15,
      "text": "\"'Miss O'Shaughnessy is an operative in my employ.'",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 407.42,
      "end": 408.94,
      "text": "Joel Cairo said indignantly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 409.62,
      "end": 410.42,
      "text": "\"'That isn't so.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 410.76,
      "end": 411.46,
      "text": "She—'"
    },
    {
      "start": 412.0,
      "end": 415.54,
      "text": "Spade interrupted him in a quite loud but still genial voice."
    },
    {
      "start": 416.86,
      "end": 418.14,
      "text": "\"'I hired her just recently.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 418.34,
      "end": 418.88,
      "text": "Yesterday."
    },
    {
      "start": 419.98,
      "end": 420.54,
      "text": "This is Mr.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 420.7,
      "end": 421.44,
      "text": "Joel Cairo."
    },
    {
      "start": 422.0,
      "end": 422.46,
      "text": "A friend."
    },
    {
      "start": 422.64,
      "end": 423.3,
      "text": "Anyhow,"
    },
    {
      "start": 423.38,
      "end": 424.86,
      "text": "an acquaintance of Thursby's."
    },
    {
      "start": 425.44,
      "end": 428.9,
      "text": "He came to me this afternoon and tried to hire me to find something"
    },
    {
      "start": 429.1,
      "end": 431.88,
      "text": "Thursby was supposed to have on him when he was bumped off."
    },
    {
      "start": 432.64,
      "end": 433.68,
      "text": "It looked queer,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 433.9,
      "end": 435.04,
      "text": "the way he put it to me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 435.16,
      "end": 436.48,
      "text": "so I wouldn't touch it."
    },
    {
      "start": 437.46,
      "end": 438.6,
      "text": "Then he pulled a gun.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 439.28,
      "end": 439.92,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 440.08,
      "end": 440.92,
      "text": "never mind that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 441.08,
      "end": 443.18,
      "text": "unless it comes to a point of laying charges"
    },
    {
      "start": 443.38,
      "end": 444.12,
      "text": "against each other."
    },
    {
      "start": 444.8,
      "end": 445.4,
      "text": "Anyway,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 445.54,
      "end": 447.72,
      "text": "after talking it over with Miss O'Shaughnessy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 447.9,
      "end": 448.96,
      "text": "I thought maybe"
    },
    {
      "start": 449.12,
      "end": 450.42,
      "text": "I could get something out of him"
    },
    {
      "start": 450.42,
      "end": 452.18,
      "text": "about Miles's and Thursby's killings,"
    },
    {
      "start": 452.52,
      "end": 454.14,
      "text": "so I asked him to come up here."
    },
    {
      "start": 455.36,
      "end": 457.68,
      "text": "Maybe we put the questions to him a little rough,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 457.82,
      "end": 459.02,
      "text": "but he wasn't hurt any,"
    },
    {
      "start": 459.32,
      "end": 461.02,
      "text": "not enough to have to cry for help."
    },
    {
      "start": 462.144,
      "end": 464.36,
      "text": "I'd already had to take his gun away from him again.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 465.92,
      "end": 466.72,
      "text": "As Spade talked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 466.8,
      "end": 469.02,
      "text": "anxiety came into Cairo's reddened face."
    },
    {
      "start": 469.82,
      "end": 471.6,
      "text": "His eyes moved jerkily up and down,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 471.7,
      "end": 474.66,
      "text": "shifting their focus uneasily between the floor and Spade's"
    },
    {
      "start": 474.76,
      "end": 475.26,
      "text": "bland face."
    },
    {
      "start": 476.672,
      "end": 479.2,
      "text": "Dundee confronted Cairo and demanded brusquely,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 479.79,
      "end": 480.14,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 480.28,
      "end": 481.42,
      "text": "what have you got to say to that?"
    },
    {
      "start": 483.008,
      "end": 484.94,
      "text": "Cairo had nothing to say for nearly a minute",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 484.94,
      "end": 486.88,
      "text": "while he stared at the lieutenant's chest."
    },
    {
      "start": 487.46,
      "end": 488.84,
      "text": "But he lifted his eyes."
    },
    {
      "start": 488.88,
      "end": 490.06,
      "text": "They were shy and wary."
    }
  ]
}